Example NPAG Output with validation

Source: R/DataDescriptions.R
NPex_val.Rd

Example output from an NPAG run with validation.

Usage

NPex_val

Format

R6 PM_result

Details

This is an R6 Pmetrics PM_result object created with PM_load after an NPAG run. The run consisted of a model with an absorptive compartment and a central compartment. There were 4 parameters in the model: lag time of absorption (Tlag1), rate constant of absorption (Ka), volume (V) with weight as a covariate, and rate constant of elmination (Ke). There were 20 subjects in the dataset. The run was 100 cycles long and did not converge. It was then validated with the $validate method for PM_result objects.

Author

Michael Neely
